{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143385964,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jCIn8jrQT0SqsJIvMHL1LKdL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation</path>\n<type>directory</type>\n<entries>\n001-memory-commands/\n002-speckit-commands/\n003-create-commands/\n004-doctor-commands/\ndescription.json\ngraph-metadata.json\nreview/\nspec.md\n\n(8 entries)\n</entries>","metadata":{"preview":"001-memory-commands/\n002-speckit-commands/\n003-create-commands/\n004-doctor-commands/\ndescription.json\ngraph-metadata.json\nreview/\nspec.md","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"directory","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation","entries":["001-memory-commands/","002-speckit-commands/","003-create-commands/","004-doctor-commands/","description.json","graph-metadata.json","review/","spec.md"],"offset":1,"totalEntries":8,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/011-command-presentation-workflow-separation","time":{"start":1781143385959,"end":1781143385963}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07c939846bb71dcb016a2a1759e3208191b354d394a89ef933"}},"id":"prt_eb46b3745001ax12zTrAQUDDZI","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","messageID":"msg_eb46b0fd1001nAbs6x5tY3tKI6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143385999,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Dh4jFOdE9MlqP1sEAkUWitqQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\n3: argument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /memory:save\n8: \n9: Thin router for canonical continuity saves.\n10: \n11: ## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n16: | Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md` | Required | Startup questions, save dashboards, result envelopes, trigger-edit display, and error rendering. |\n17: \n18: Before rendering any prompt, dashboard, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n19: \n20: ## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n21: \n22: Inputs:\n23: - `$ARGUMENTS` may contain an explicit spec folder.\n24: - If `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, resolve the active spec folder using Gate 3 carry-over first, session file evidence second, and a targeted user question only when ambiguous.\n25: \n26: Outputs:\n27: - Default response is a save plan: target route, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions.\n28: - Explicit apply/full-auto may run `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` with AI-authored JSON.\n29: - Immediate retrieval freshness may use `memory_index_scan({ specFolder, includeSpecDocs: true, force: false })` after the save.\n30: \n31: ## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n32: \n33: 1. Resolve and validate `target_folder`.\n34: 2. Check topic/folder alignment and stop for confirmation on mismatch.\n35: 3. Extract session summary, key decisions, modified files, trigger phrases, technical context, tool calls, and notable exchanges.\n36: 4. Choose route category: `narrative_progress`, `narrative_delivery`, `decision`, `handover_state`, `research_finding`, `task_update`, `metadata_only`, or `drop`.\n37: 5. In default mode, return the save plan without mutating.\n38: 6. In explicit apply/full-auto mode, execute the canonical save script, inspect the post-save quality review, patch HIGH issues when practical, then refresh index visibility through MCP.\n39: 7. Render the result using the presentation asset.\n40: \n41: ## 4. HARD RULES\n42: \n43: - Do not use standalone `memory/*.md` files as save destinations.\n44: - Do not claim an automatic hook save unless current hook evidence proves it.\n45: - Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n46: - Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n47: - Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for retention cleanup.\n48: \n49: ## 5. TOOL MAP\n50: \n51: | Need | Tool or Script |\n52: | --- | --- |\n53: | Canonical save apply | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` |\n54: | Immediate index refresh | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan` |\n55: | Single-file indexing fallback | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save` |\n56: | Trigger phrase correction | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update` |\n57: \n58: ## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n59: \n60: - `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n61: - `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n62: - `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n63: - `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.\n\n(End of file - total 63 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# /memory:save\n\nThin router for canonical continuity saves.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md` | Required | Startup questions, save dashboards, result envelopes, trigger-edit display, and error rendering. |\n\nBefore rendering any prompt, dashboard, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/save.md","text":"---\ndescription: Save current conversation context into canonical spec-doc continuity surfaces with semantic indexing\nargument-hint: \"<spec-folder>\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Edit, Bash, Task, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_stats, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update\n---\n\n# /memory:save\n\nThin router for canonical continuity saves.\n\n## 1. ROUTING ASSETS\n\n| Asset | Path | Status | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| Workflow | _No memory workflow YAML exists in this checkout_ | Missing upstream asset | Keep routing in this file until a workflow YAML is introduced by a separate workflow-asset change. Do not invent or edit YAML from this command. |\n| Presentation | `.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md` | Required | Startup questions, save dashboards, result envelopes, trigger-edit display, and error rendering. |\n\nBefore rendering any prompt, dashboard, or result block, read the presentation asset and follow it as the display source of truth.\n\n## 2. ROUTER CONTRACT\n\nInputs:\n- `$ARGUMENTS` may contain an explicit spec folder.\n- If `$ARGUMENTS` is empty, resolve the active spec folder using Gate 3 carry-over first, session file evidence second, and a targeted user question only when ambiguous.\n\nOutputs:\n- Default response is a save plan: target route, proposed edits, blockers, advisories, and follow-up actions.\n- Explicit apply/full-auto may run `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` with AI-authored JSON.\n- Immediate retrieval freshness may use `memory_index_scan({ specFolder, includeSpecDocs: true, force: false })` after the save.\n\n## 3. WORKFLOW ROUTING\n\n1. Resolve and validate `target_folder`.\n2. Check topic/folder alignment and stop for confirmation on mismatch.\n3. Extract session summary, key decisions, modified files, trigger phrases, technical context, tool calls, and notable exchanges.\n4. Choose route category: `narrative_progress`, `narrative_delivery`, `decision`, `handover_state`, `research_finding`, `task_update`, `metadata_only`, or `drop`.\n5. In default mode, return the save plan without mutating.\n6. In explicit apply/full-auto mode, execute the canonical save script, inspect the post-save quality review, patch HIGH issues when practical, then refresh index visibility through MCP.\n7. Render the result using the presentation asset.\n\n## 4. HARD RULES\n\n- Do not use standalone `memory/*.md` files as save destinations.\n- Do not claim an automatic hook save unless current hook evidence proves it.\n- Do not open raw SQLite or edit memory DB files.\n- Do not create or modify workflow YAML from this command.\n- Use `/memory:manage retention-sweep` for retention cleanup.\n\n## 5. TOOL MAP\n\n| Need | Tool or Script |\n| --- | --- |\n| Canonical save apply | `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js` |\n| Immediate index refresh | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan` |\n| Single-file indexing fallback | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save` |\n| Trigger phrase correction | `mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_update` |\n\n## 6. RELATED COMMANDS\n\n- `/memory:search`: Intent-aware context retrieval and analysis tools.\n- `/memory:manage`: Database management, checkpoints, ingest, retention, and health.\n- `/memory:learn`: Constitutional rules.\n- `/speckit:resume`: Session recovery and continuation.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":63,"totalLines":63,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/save.md","time":{"start":1781143385987,"end":1781143385998}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07c939846bb71dcb016a2a1759e32c8191b8930f13510ee064"}},"id":"prt_eb46b3769001fpEbrW9VXbhk2J","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","messageID":"msg_eb46b0fd1001nAbs6x5tY3tKI6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143386000,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_AKYQzlGiDVQTf023QLSTfz6T","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Memory Save Presentation Contract\n2: \n3: Single source of truth for `/memory:save` startup questions, dashboards, and result displays.\n4: \n5: ## 1. Startup Question Policy\n6: \n7: Use the shortest prompt that resolves the target folder.\n8: \n9: | Situation | Display |\n10: | --- | --- |\n11: | Explicit folder in `$ARGUMENTS` | No startup question. Validate the folder and continue. |\n12: | Gate 3 carry-over exists | Announce `Using active spec folder from this session: <folder>` and continue. |\n13: | One clear session folder from touched files | Ask `Save context to <folder>? [Y/n]`. |\n14: | Multiple plausible folders | Ask `Which spec folder should receive this save?` and list only the candidate folders. |\n15: | No plausible folder | Ask for a target spec folder and stop until answered. |\n16: \n17: Do not show a long option menu unless there are multiple candidates.\n18: \n19: ## 2. Save Plan Display\n20: \n21: ```text\n22: MEMORY:SAVE PLAN\n23: --------------------------------------------------\n24: Folder      <spec_folder>\n25: Mode        plan-only\n26: Route       <route_category>\n27: Targets     <target_1>, <target_2>\n28: \n29: Proposed edits\n30: - <edit summary>\n31: \n32: Follow-up\n33: - <apply|refresh-graph|reindex|none>\n34: \n35: STATUS=OK ACTION=plan TARGET=<spec_folder>\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ## 3. Apply Result Display\n39: \n40: ```text\n41: MEMORY:SAVE\n42: --------------------------------------------------\n43: Folder      <spec_folder>\n44: Targets     <target_1>, <target_2>, <target_3>\n45: Indexing    <indexed|deferred|failed>\n46: \n47: Anchors\n48: - <anchor_1>\n49: - <anchor_2>\n50: \n51: Triggers\n52: <phrase_1> | <phrase_2> | <phrase_3>\n53: \n54: STATUS=OK TARGETS=<count> ANCHORS=<count>\n55: ```\n56: \n57: ## 4. Trigger Edit Display\n58: \n59: ```text\n60: MEMORY:TRIGGERS\n61: --------------------------------------------------\n62: Record      #<id> \"<spec_doc_title>\"\n63: \n64: Current triggers\n65: 1. <phrase_1>\n66: 2. <phrase_2>\n67: 3. <phrase_3>\n68: \n69: Actions: [a] add | [r] remove number | [s] save | [d] done\n70: STATUS=OK ID=<id> TRIGGERS=<count>\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ## 5. Error Display\n74: \n75: ```text\n76: MEMORY:SAVE\n77: --------------------------------------------------\n78: FAIL        <short reason>\n79: Recovery    <next safe action>\n80: \n81: STATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"<message>\"\n82: ```\n83: \n84: ## 6. Display Rules\n85: \n86: - Keep output parseable: stable labels, one status line, no decorative menu dumps.\n87: - Report save quality review issues only when returned by the save script or tool.\n88: - Label deferred indexing honestly; saved documents remain durable even if retrieval is stale.\n89: - End with one concise next action, not an open-ended option list.\n\n(End of file - total 89 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Memory Save Presentation Contract\n\nSingle source of truth for `/memory:save` startup questions, dashboards, and result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Question Policy\n\nUse the shortest prompt that resolves the target folder.\n\n| Situation | Display |\n| --- | --- |\n| Explicit folder in `$ARGUMENTS` | No startup question. Validate the folder and continue. |\n| Gate 3 carry-over exists | Announce `Using active spec folder from this session: <folder>` and continue. |\n| One clear session folder from touched files | Ask `Save context to <folder>? [Y/n]`. |\n| Multiple plausible folders | Ask `Which spec folder should receive this save?` and list only the candidate folders. |\n| No plausible folder | Ask for a target spec folder and stop until answered. |\n\nDo not show a long option menu unless there are multiple candidates.\n\n## 2. Save Plan Display\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md","text":"# Memory Save Presentation Contract\n\nSingle source of truth for `/memory:save` startup questions, dashboards, and result displays.\n\n## 1. Startup Question Policy\n\nUse the shortest prompt that resolves the target folder.\n\n| Situation | Display |\n| --- | --- |\n| Explicit folder in `$ARGUMENTS` | No startup question. Validate the folder and continue. |\n| Gate 3 carry-over exists | Announce `Using active spec folder from this session: <folder>` and continue. |\n| One clear session folder from touched files | Ask `Save context to <folder>? [Y/n]`. |\n| Multiple plausible folders | Ask `Which spec folder should receive this save?` and list only the candidate folders. |\n| No plausible folder | Ask for a target spec folder and stop until answered. |\n\nDo not show a long option menu unless there are multiple candidates.\n\n## 2. Save Plan Display\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SAVE PLAN\n--------------------------------------------------\nFolder      <spec_folder>\nMode        plan-only\nRoute       <route_category>\nTargets     <target_1>, <target_2>\n\nProposed edits\n- <edit summary>\n\nFollow-up\n- <apply|refresh-graph|reindex|none>\n\nSTATUS=OK ACTION=plan TARGET=<spec_folder>\n```\n\n## 3. Apply Result Display\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SAVE\n--------------------------------------------------\nFolder      <spec_folder>\nTargets     <target_1>, <target_2>, <target_3>\nIndexing    <indexed|deferred|failed>\n\nAnchors\n- <anchor_1>\n- <anchor_2>\n\nTriggers\n<phrase_1> | <phrase_2> | <phrase_3>\n\nSTATUS=OK TARGETS=<count> ANCHORS=<count>\n```\n\n## 4. Trigger Edit Display\n\n```text\nMEMORY:TRIGGERS\n--------------------------------------------------\nRecord      #<id> \"<spec_doc_title>\"\n\nCurrent triggers\n1. <phrase_1>\n2. <phrase_2>\n3. <phrase_3>\n\nActions: [a] add | [r] remove number | [s] save | [d] done\nSTATUS=OK ID=<id> TRIGGERS=<count>\n```\n\n## 5. Error Display\n\n```text\nMEMORY:SAVE\n--------------------------------------------------\nFAIL        <short reason>\nRecovery    <next safe action>\n\nSTATUS=FAIL ERROR=\"<message>\"\n```\n\n## 6. Display Rules\n\n- Keep output parseable: stable labels, one status line, no decorative menu dumps.\n- Report save quality review issues only when returned by the save script or tool.\n- Label deferred indexing honestly; saved documents remain durable even if retrieval is stale.\n- End with one concise next action, not an open-ended option list.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":89,"totalLines":89,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/memory/assets/save_presentation.md","time":{"start":1781143385990,"end":1781143385999}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07c939846bb71dcb016a2a1759e3348191bbb081b565a333cd"}},"id":"prt_eb46b3785001Jiw6HG5nL9vxEH","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","messageID":"msg_eb46b0fd1001nAbs6x5tY3tKI6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143386009,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_LcWqcdHJRdfX3terbz40EVaK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-context, :with-phases.\n3: argument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # SpecKit Plan\n8: \n9: Thin router for the SpecKit planning workflow. This command resolves the execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n10: \n11: ## 1. Router Contract\n12: \n13: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n14: \n15: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n16: \n17: ## 2. Owned Assets\n18: \n19: | Purpose | Asset |\n20: |---------|-------|\n21: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md` |\n22: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n23: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n24: \n25: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n26: \n27: ## 3. Mode Routing\n28: \n29: 1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n30: 2. Treat `:with-context`, `:with-phases`, `--intake-only`, `--phases`, `--phase-names`, `--phase-folder`, `--spec-folder`, `--level`, `--start-state`, `--repair-mode`, and relationship flags as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n31: 3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n32: 4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n33: 5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n34: \n35: ## 4. Execution Targets\n36: \n37: | Mode | Workflow |\n38: |------|----------|\n39: | `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n40: | `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n41: \n42: ## 5. Presentation Boundary\n43: \n44: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md`:\n45: \n46: - Startup-question wording and reply format.\n47: - `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n48: - Checkpoint and dashboard display templates, including deep-context and phase-decomposition checkpoints.\n49: - Success and failure result templates.\n50: - Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n51: \n52: ## 6. Workflow Summary\n53: \n54: The YAML workflow runs planning from intake through context refresh and terminates before implementation. If a user requests implementation after planning, route to `/speckit:implement`; do not start implementation from this command.\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-context, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Plan\n\nThin router for the SpecKit planning workflow. This command resolves the execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","text":"---\ndescription: Planning workflow (8 steps): spec through plan only. Modes :auto, :confirm, :with-context, :with-phases.\nargument-hint: \"<feature-description> [:auto|:confirm] [:with-context] [:with-phases] [--intake-only] [--phases N] [--phase-names list] [--phase-folder=<path>] [--spec-folder=PATH] [--level=1|2|3|3+] [--start-state=STATE] [--repair-mode=MODE] [--record-relationships=yes|no] [--depends-on=IDs] [--related-to=IDs] [--supersedes=IDs] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, memory_context, memory_search, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_save, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_index_scan\n---\n\n# SpecKit Plan\n\nThin router for the SpecKit planning workflow. This command resolves the execution mode, loads the presentation contract, then executes the owned workflow YAML.\n\n## 1. Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Agent dispatch, workflow steps, and artifact-writing behavior are owned by the workflow YAML assets.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, checkpoints, dashboards, success output, failure output, or next-step prompts.\n\n## 2. Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md` |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## 3. Mode Routing\n\n1. Parse `$ARGUMENTS` for `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n2. Treat `:with-context`, `:with-phases`, `--intake-only`, `--phases`, `--phase-names`, `--phase-folder`, `--spec-folder`, `--level`, `--start-state`, `--repair-mode`, and relationship flags as workflow inputs, not execution modes.\n3. If no mode suffix is present, use the presentation contract's startup prompt to ask for execution mode.\n4. For `:auto`, resolve required setup inputs using the presentation contract's auto-resolution rules before loading YAML.\n5. Load the selected workflow asset and execute it step by step.\n\n## 4. Execution Targets\n\n| Mode | Workflow |\n|------|----------|\n| `:auto` | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_auto.yaml` |\n| `:confirm` or interactive choice | `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_confirm.yaml` |\n\n## 5. Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/speckit/assets/speckit_plan_presentation.md`:\n\n- Startup-question wording and reply format.\n- `:auto` pre-bound setup answer schema, default table, targeted-ask rules, and fail-fast display.\n- Checkpoint and dashboard display templates, including deep-context and phase-decomposition checkpoints.\n- Success and failure result templates.\n- Next-step suggestions and final user prompt wording.\n\n## 6. Workflow Summary\n\nThe YAML workflow runs planning from intake through context refresh and terminates before implementation. If a user requests implementation after planning, route to `/speckit:implement`; do not start implementation from this command.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":54,"totalLines":54,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/speckit/plan.md","time":{"start":1781143386002,"end":1781143386008}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07c939846bb71dcb016a2a1759e33c8191b8bd043ad1a4018b"}},"id":"prt_eb46b378b001p3kHsUW59kAyNx","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","messageID":"msg_eb46b0fd1001nAbs6x5tY3tKI6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143386015,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6FOml6Xd0cEi7bs7rxwsPqdL","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/agent.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/agent.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Create a new OpenCode agent with frontmatter, tool permissions, behavioral rules. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<agent_name> [agent_description] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # /create:agent Router\n8: \n9: This command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n10: \n11: ## Routing Assets\n12: \n13: | Asset | Path | Purpose |\n14: | --- | --- | --- |\n15: | Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, and completion display |\n16: | Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml` | Autonomous workflow execution |\n17: | Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed workflow execution |\n18: \n19: ## Execution Order\n20: \n21: 1. Read `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md`.\n22: 2. Run the presentation contract's Phase 0 verification and setup resolution.\n23: 3. Resolve execution mode from `$ARGUMENTS` or the setup answer: `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n24: 4. Load exactly one workflow YAML:\n25:    - `:auto` -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml`\n26:    - `:confirm` or omitted mode -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml`\n27: 5. Execute the selected YAML step by step.\n28: 6. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, setup/status dashboards, and final result display.\n29: \n30: ## Routing Rules\n31: \n32: - Do not dispatch agents from this router.\n33: - Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n34: - If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n35: - The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns user-visible wording and layout.\n36: \n37: User request: {{args}}\n\n(End of file - total 37 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Create a new OpenCode agent with frontmatter, tool permissions, behavioral rules. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<agent_name> [agent_description] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n---\n\n# /create:agent Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n\n## Routing Assets\n\n| Asset | Path | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, and completion display |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml` | Autonomous workflow execution |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed workflow execution |\n\n## Execution Order\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/create/agent.md","text":"---\ndescription: Create a new OpenCode agent with frontmatter, tool permissions, behavioral rules. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<agent_name> [agent_description] [:auto|:confirm] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TodoWrite\n---\n\n# /create:agent Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It separates execution routing from user-facing presentation.\n\n## Routing Assets\n\n| Asset | Path | Purpose |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| Presentation contract | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md` | Startup questions, setup dashboard, and completion display |\n| Auto workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml` | Autonomous workflow execution |\n| Confirm workflow | `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml` | Interactive checkpointed workflow execution |\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. Read `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_presentation.md`.\n2. Run the presentation contract's Phase 0 verification and setup resolution.\n3. Resolve execution mode from `$ARGUMENTS` or the setup answer: `:auto` or `:confirm`.\n4. Load exactly one workflow YAML:\n   - `:auto` -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_auto.yaml`\n   - `:confirm` or omitted mode -> `.opencode/commands/create/assets/create_agent_confirm.yaml`\n5. Execute the selected YAML step by step.\n6. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, setup/status dashboards, and final result display.\n\n## Routing Rules\n\n- Do not dispatch agents from this router.\n- Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n- If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n- The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns user-visible wording and layout.\n\nUser request: {{args}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":37,"totalLines":37,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/create/agent.md","time":{"start":1781143386010,"end":1781143386014}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07c939846bb71dcb016a2a1759e344819183a3e5fef590b3cf"}},"id":"prt_eb46b37920017gZwPx6517CgNW","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","messageID":"msg_eb46b0fd1001nAbs6x5tY3tKI6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781143386016,"sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_S0iZBmusUhRxOnGxczHf6Gg8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md","offset":1,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Install or repair MCP servers via /doctor:mcp <install|debug> sub-action routing.\n3: argument-hint: \"<install|debug> [--server <name>] [--runtime <name>] [--fix]\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write\n5: ---\n6: <!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n7: \n8: # /doctor:mcp Router\n9: \n10: This command is a thin router. It resolves the MCP sub-action and setup values, then loads the matching workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n11: \n12: ## Router Contract\n13: \n14: Do not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n15: \n16: Load the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, MCP health dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n17: \n18: ## Owned Assets\n19: \n20: | Purpose | Asset |\n21: |---------|-------|\n22: | Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md` |\n23: | Install workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml` |\n24: | Debug workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml` |\n25: \n26: No workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n27: \n28: ## Execution Order\n29: \n30: 1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`.\n31: 2. Parse the first positional token from `$ARGUMENTS` as `sub_action`.\n32: 3. If `sub_action` is missing, ask the presentation contract's sub-action prompt and wait.\n33: 4. If `sub_action` is not `install` or `debug`, render the presentation contract's unknown-sub-action failure and stop.\n34: 5. Bind the workflow asset:\n35:    - `install` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml`\n36:    - `debug` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`\n37: 6. Parse remaining flags using only the selected sub-action schema:\n38:    - `install`: `--server <name>`, `--runtime <name>`\n39:    - `debug`: `--fix`, `--server <name>`\n40: 7. Reject cross-sub-action flags before YAML load using the presentation contract's error wording.\n41: 8. Load the selected workflow YAML and execute it step by step.\n42: 9. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, and next-step display.\n43: \n44: ## Routing Rules\n45: \n46: - The sub-action is positional and must be parsed before flags.\n47: - No mode suffix is supported.\n48: - `install` and `debug` have overlapping `--server` flag names; keep their schemas separate.\n49: - If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n50: - This command repairs MCP infrastructure itself; subsystem database diagnostics stay under `/doctor <target>` and `/doctor:update`.\n51: - The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n52: \n53: ## Presentation Boundary\n54: \n55: The following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`:\n56: \n57: - Sub-action menu, accepted answers, and cancellation display.\n58: - Unknown-sub-action and cross-sub-action flag errors.\n59: - MCP assessment, install, repair, verification, and final-report display templates.\n60: - Examples, troubleshooting display, and next-step text.\n61: \n62: User request: {{args}}\n\n(End of file - total 62 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Install or repair MCP servers via /doctor:mcp <install|debug> sub-action routing.\nargument-hint: \"<install|debug> [--server <name>] [--runtime <name>] [--fix]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor:mcp Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves the MCP sub-action and setup values, then loads the matching workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, MCP health dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md","text":"---\ndescription: Install or repair MCP servers via /doctor:mcp <install|debug> sub-action routing.\nargument-hint: \"<install|debug> [--server <name>] [--runtime <name>] [--fix]\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Bash, Grep, Glob, Edit, Write\n---\n<!-- skill_agent: system-spec-kit -->\n\n# /doctor:mcp Router\n\nThis command is a thin router. It resolves the MCP sub-action and setup values, then loads the matching workflow YAML and the presentation contract.\n\n## Router Contract\n\nDo not dispatch agents from this Markdown file. Do not edit workflow YAML while executing this command.\n\nLoad the presentation contract before showing startup questions, setup dashboards, approval prompts, MCP health dashboards, result summaries, or next-step text.\n\n## Owned Assets\n\n| Purpose | Asset |\n|---------|-------|\n| Presentation source of truth | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md` |\n| Install workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml` |\n| Debug workflow | `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml` |\n\nNo workflow-asset gap exists for this command.\n\n## Execution Order\n\n1. Read `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`.\n2. Parse the first positional token from `$ARGUMENTS` as `sub_action`.\n3. If `sub_action` is missing, ask the presentation contract's sub-action prompt and wait.\n4. If `sub_action` is not `install` or `debug`, render the presentation contract's unknown-sub-action failure and stop.\n5. Bind the workflow asset:\n   - `install` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_install.yaml`\n   - `debug` -> `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_debug.yaml`\n6. Parse remaining flags using only the selected sub-action schema:\n   - `install`: `--server <name>`, `--runtime <name>`\n   - `debug`: `--fix`, `--server <name>`\n7. Reject cross-sub-action flags before YAML load using the presentation contract's error wording.\n8. Load the selected workflow YAML and execute it step by step.\n9. Use the presentation contract, not this router, for user prompts, dashboards, result summaries, and next-step display.\n\n## Routing Rules\n\n- The sub-action is positional and must be parsed before flags.\n- No mode suffix is supported.\n- `install` and `debug` have overlapping `--server` flag names; keep their schemas separate.\n- If any referenced asset is missing, stop and report the missing path.\n- This command repairs MCP infrastructure itself; subsystem database diagnostics stay under `/doctor <target>` and `/doctor:update`.\n- The YAML owns workflow behavior; the presentation Markdown owns visible wording and layout.\n\n## Presentation Boundary\n\nThe following content lives only in `.opencode/commands/doctor/assets/doctor_mcp_presentation.md`:\n\n- Sub-action menu, accepted answers, and cancellation display.\n- Unknown-sub-action and cross-sub-action flag errors.\n- MCP assessment, install, repair, verification, and final-report display templates.\n- Examples, troubleshooting display, and next-step text.\n\nUser request: {{args}}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":62,"totalLines":62,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/doctor/mcp.md","time":{"start":1781143386012,"end":1781143386015}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07c939846bb71dcb016a2a1759e34c8191bea22e3a11fdec68"}},"id":"prt_eb46b379b001NPjQ424BV2Yx20","sessionID":"ses_14b95d469ffeKSdlrFqwWXsS50","messageID":"msg_eb46b0fd1001nAbs6x5tY3tKI6"}}
