n contract used by every user-invokable `/command:*:auto` surface in spec-kit (`/spec_kit:*`, `/create:*`, `/deep:*`). Each command's §0 cites this contract and supplies only its own per-field Default Resolution Table + `PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS:` field list. The contract semantics, marker grammar, error format, and verification protocol live here.\n\n  Line 186: - Cross-command `:auto` integration (e.g. `/spec_kit:plan:auto` chained into `/spec_kit:implement:auto`) — separate contract concern.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/hooks/claude/README.md:\n  Line 61: For packet work, the operator-facing recovery surface remains `/spec_kit:resume`, with continuity rebuilt from `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/INSTALL_GUIDE.md:\n  Line 154: | Codex | `.codex/config.toml` | Checked-in MCP config plus native `SessionStart` and `UserPromptSubmit` hooks when `[features].codex_hooks = true` in `~/.codex/config.toml` and `~/.codex/hooks.json` is wired. When those hooks are unavailable, recover via `/spec_kit:resume` or `session_bootstrap`. |\n\n  Line 837: **Behind the scenes:** The AI uses `/spec_kit:resume` as the canonical recovery surface. That flow reconstructs packet context from `handover.md`, then `_memory.continuity`, then the canonical spec docs before it falls through to deeper MCP retrieval.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/22--context-preservation/cross-runtime-fallback.md:\n  Line 5: phase_018_change: \"Reframed recovery so hook-limited runtimes fall back through /spec_kit:resume and the canonical packet continuity ladder.\"\n\n  Line 25: - Pass/fail: PASS: Each runtime is correctly detected from env vars, hookPolicy matches the current runtime/config reality, Copilot custom-instructions refresh is recognized as the enabled prompt-time transport, and fallback only appears when hooks are unavailable or disabled_by_scope and routes through /spec_kit:resume; FAIL: Any runtime misidentified, hookPolicy incorrect, or hooks reported as available for a runtime/config state that should fall back\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/16--tooling-and-scripts/spec-folder-literal-naming-cli-driven-slug.md:\n  Line 19: - Real user request: `An operator gives a deliberately ambiguous task to an external CLI agent that should trigger /spec_kit:plan phase decomposition. Verify the AI proposes phase names with specific subject tokens, NOT generic placeholders.`\n\n  Line 36:   .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_plan_auto.yaml \\\n\n  Line 37:   .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_plan_confirm.yaml \\\n\n  Line 38:   .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_complete_auto.yaml \\\n\n  Line 39:   .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_complete_confirm.yaml\n\n  Line 51: You are an AI coding agent connected to the system-spec-kit MCP. The operator has asked you to plan work for the following task using /spec_kit:plan :with-phases (3 phases):\n\n  Line 77: You are an AI coding agent connected to the system-spec-kit MCP. The operator has asked you to plan work for the following task using /spec_kit:plan :with-phases (3 phases):\n\n  Line 106: You are an AI coding agent connected to the system-spec-kit MCP. The operator has asked you to plan work for the following task using /spec_kit:plan :with-phases (3 phases):\n\n  Line 129:   --prompt \"You are an AI coding agent connected to the system-spec-kit MCP. The operator has asked you to plan work for the following task using /spec_kit:plan :with-phases (3 phases):\n\n  Line 142: claude -p \"You are an AI coding agent connected to the system-spec-kit MCP. The operator has asked you to plan work for the following task using /spec_kit:plan :with-phases (3 phases):\n\n  Line 209: - If a CLI returns generic stoplist slugs: confirm that CLI's MCP wiring surfaces the `spec_kit_plan_auto.yaml` activity. Run `grep -F \"LITERAL phase names\" .opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_plan_auto.yaml` and confirm at least 1 match.\n\n  Line 210: - If the YAML is present but the CLI ignores it: re-run with explicit reference to `/spec_kit:plan :with-phases` in the user prompt. The YAML activity fires only when the command route is active.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/22--context-preservation/session-start-priming.md:\n  Line 28: The SessionStart hook routes by `source` field from stdin JSON. For `compact`: reads cached payload from hook state, injects, clears cache. For `startup`: outputs Spec Kit Memory tool overview. For `resume`: loads lastSpecFolder from hook state and points recovery back to `/spec_kit:resume` with the `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs` chain. For `clear`: minimal output. Token budget: 2000 for startup/resume, 4000 for compact.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/22--context-preservation/tool-routing-enforcement.md:\n  Line 20: The implementation addresses the root cause of AI tool misjudgment by adding active enforcement at the MCP layer. Five complementary layers work together: (1) buildServerInstructions() injects routing rules into every MCP session, (2) PrimePackage includes routingRules directives during session priming, (3) tool response hints detect code-search patterns and redirect to appropriate tools, (4) runtime instruction files (CLAUDE.md, CODEX.md) contain active decision trees, and (5) the canonical resume/bootstrap surfaces (`/spec_kit:resume`, `session_bootstrap()`, `session_resume()`) reuse the same routing contract instead of a separate bootstrap agent. This makes correct tool selection structurally enforced rather than instructionally suggested.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/22--context-preservation/cross-runtime-fallback.md:\n  Line 18: Claude Code uses native hooks. Codex CLI now has native `SessionStart` and `UserPromptSubmit` hooks when `codex_hooks = true` and user-level `~/.codex/hooks.json` registers the Spec Kit commands; older or restricted deployments fall back to the tool path or prompt wrapper. Copilot CLI uses the shared `.claude/settings.local.json` matcher wrappers as its effective prompt/startup surface; those Copilot-safe wrappers carry top-level `type`, `bash`, and `timeoutSec` fields, and the `UserPromptSubmit` and `SessionStart` wrappers run the Spec Kit writer commands because Copilot hook stdout is not prompt-mutating. OpenCode uses plugin-based hooks (`@opencode-ai/plugin` at `.opencode/plugins/spec-kit-compact-code-graph.js`). When hooks fail or are unavailable in any runtime, recover through the canonical tool-based path starting with `/spec_kit:resume`, which resolves `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`; `session_bootstrap()` and `session_resume()` remain the lower-level recovery surfaces for structural bootstrap and detailed merged state. Runtime detection identifies the active runtime and its current hook policy.\n\n  Line 24: Runtime detection is the source of truth for hook-aware fallback. It identifies the active runtime, classifies the current hook policy as `enabled`, `disabled_by_scope`, `unavailable`, or `unknown`, and then lets packet recovery fall back through `/spec_kit:resume` and the `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs` chain when runtime hooks are missing. The contract is intentionally runtime-specific rather than \"all shells behave the same.\" For Copilot, `enabled` means the shared `.claude/settings.local.json` wrappers are present in a Copilot-safe shape and can run the top-level writer commands on `UserPromptSubmit` and `SessionStart` to refresh managed custom instructions and compact-cache state; it does not mean hook stdout injects `additionalContext`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/22--context-preservation/category-overview.md:\n  Line 26: The shipped surface now includes hook scripts, code graph modules, MCP tools, budget allocator, tree-sitter parser with regex fallback, query-intent routing, auto-trigger, session health/resume/bootstrap tools, the structural ready/stale/missing contract, and startup-brief follow-ons. Recovery treats `/spec_kit:resume` as the canonical surface and follows `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs` before widening to broader memory artifacts.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.0.0.md:\n  Line 5: Alongside the memory rewrite, the search stack got smarter, the code graph got safer to traverse, deep-loop skills became fully auditable, and every CLI skill now runs a quality check on its prompts before talking to external models. A cleanup pass on the skill advisor removed dead routing code and added coverage for the kinds of phrases people actually type. The intake command surface also consolidated: `/spec_kit:start` is gone, replaced by `/spec_kit:plan --intake-only` backed by a shared intake contract. \n\n  Line 19: | **Command Graph** | `/spec_kit:start` deleted, merged into `/spec_kit:plan --intake-only`. Shared intake contract consolidates three parallel intake surfaces into one canonical module. |\n\n  Line 70: `/spec_kit:handover` and `/spec_kit:debug` are gone. So are the `@handover` and `@speckit` agents across all four runtimes, 15 paths total.\n\n  Line 76: `/spec_kit:complete` loses its `:auto-debug` flag. If implementation fails three times, the workflow surfaces the diagnostic and you decide whether to dispatch `@debug` yourself.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.4.1.0.md:\n  Line 475: - **`/spec_kit:start`** is gone (since v3.4.0.0). Use `/spec_kit:plan --intake-only`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.2.1.0.md:\n  Line 23: `/create:changelog`, `/spec_kit:implement`, and `/spec_kit:complete` could not speak consistently about packet-local history if the generator, templates, and workflow docs were updated in isolation. All three command surfaces were updated in the same pass so packet-aware closeout now teaches one consistent behavior: implementation summary plus nested packet changelog, with root and phase naming handled by the shipped generator instead of manual improvisation.\n\n  Line 111: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/implement.md`                                               | Updated implementation closeout guidance to generate nested changelogs for packet-aware targets                          |\n\n  Line 112: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/complete.md`                                                | Updated completion closeout guidance to generate nested changelogs for packet-aware targets                              |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v2+/v2.3.0.6.md:\n  Line 19: This release updates Command path added. Phase command path added: /spec_kit:phase command and workflow assets were introduced for autonomous and confirm-style flows. This matters because the release is clearer and easier to work with.\n\n  Line 34: People needed clearer guidance about Existing commands updated. Existing commands updated: /spec_kit:plan, /spec_kit:implement, /spec_kit:complete, and /spec_kit:resume were updated for phase-aware behavior. This matters because the release notes and instructions are easier to read and trust.\n\n  Line 62: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/phase.md` | New phase command. |\n\n  Line 63: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_phase_auto.yaml` | Autonomous phase workflow asset. |\n\n  Line 64: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/assets/spec_kit_phase_confirm.yaml` | Interactive phase workflow asset. |\n\n  Line 65: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/plan.md` | Gate 3 Option E and phase-folder path handling. |\n\n  Line 66: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/resume.md` | Phase-aware folder detection guidance. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v2+/v2.3.0.5.md:\n  Line 39: People needed clearer guidance about Command guidance aligned. Command guidance aligned: /spec_kit:resume and /spec_kit:handover guidance was verified against detector behavior. This matters because the release notes and instructions are easier to read and trust.\n\n  Line 56: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/resume.md` | Verified command guidance alignment with deterministic session selection. |\n\n  Line 57: | `.opencode/commands/spec_kit/handover.md` | Verified command guidance alignment with selection/fallback behavior. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v3.0.0.3.md:\n  Line 45: | `.agents/commands/spec_kit/*.toml` + `.agents/workflows/*.md` | Modified | Wrapper and workflow alignment |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/changelog/v2+/v2.2.8.0.md:\n  Line 9: 13 YAML prompt assets was no longer needed in its old form. Compressed from 13,333 to 5,378 lines (59.7% reduction) in command/spec_kit/assets/ using compact YAML flow notation ({key: value}, [a, b]), removed Mermaid diagrams (never rendered in CLI), decorative separators, verbose description fields. This matters because the project becomes smaller and easier to maintain.\n\n  Li